12/03/2008
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Defence ministers from across Southeast Europe met in Sofia on Tuesday (March 11th), under Bulgaria's chairmanship of the South-East European Co-operation Process. Prime Minister Sergey Stanishev opened the meeting by saying regional security should be viewed as an integral whole. Bulgarian Defence Minister Vesselin Bliznakov said his counterparts have agreed that the process of adopting Euro-Atlantic values, such as transparency and openness in defence policy, has deepened. The ministers adopted a joint declaration committing their countries to boost co-operation aimed at strengthening regional security and further developing Euro-Atlantic prospects. (Trud - 12/03/08; BGNES - 11/03/08)
